The paper proposes a deep learning method for predicting stock returns, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the method uses LSTM, which is a type of recurrent neural network, and LRP, which is a technique for interpreting deep learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these sub-categories are closely related to deep learning. Additionally, the paper involves time series analysis, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper includes an empirical analysis of the Japanese stock market, which involves statistical analysis, suggesting that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be a relevant sub-category.
